FR940525-2-00035 FR940525-2-00027 [FEMA&hyph;1021&hyph;DR] Virginia; Amendment to a Major Disaster Declaration AGENCY: Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA). ACTION: Notice. SUMMARY: This notice amends the notice of a major disaster for the Commonwealth of Virginia, (FEMA&hyph;1021&hyph;DR), dated April 11, 1994, and related determinations. EFFECTIVE DATE: May 17, 1994. FOR FURTHER INFORMATION CONTACT: Pauline C. Campbell, Response and Recovery Directorate, Federal Emergency Management Agency, Washington, DC 20472, (202) 646&hyph;3606. SUPPLEMENTARY INFORMATION: The notice of a major disaster for the Commonwealth of Virginia dated April 11, 1994, is hereby amended to include the following areas among those areas determined to have been adversely affected by the catastrophe declared a major disaster by the President in his declaration of April 11, 1994:. The counties of Hanover, Montgomery, Pittsylvania, and Roanoke for Public Assistance. (Catalog of Federal Domestic Assistance No. 83.516, Disaster Assistance) Richard W. Krimm, Associate Director, Response and Recovery Directorate. [FR Doc. 94&hyph;12765 Filed 5&hyph;24&hyph;94; 8:45 am] BILLING CODE 6718&hyph;02&hyph;M
